  { '@type': 'Question', name: 'Why combine turmeric and ginger together?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Turmeric and ginger are both members of the Zingiberaceae family and share anti-inflammatory properties, but they work through different molecular mechanisms. Turmeric\'s curcumin inhibits NF-kB (a master regulator of inflammatory gene expression) and COX-2 (the enzyme targeted by NSAIDs like ibuprofen). Ginger\'s gingerols and shogaols inhibit COX-2 and LOX (lipoxygenase), blocking both the prostaglandin and leukotriene inflammatory pathways. Together, they provide broader anti-inflammatory coverage than either alone — blocking NF-kB + COX-2 + LOX simultaneously. Additionally, ginger improves gastric motility and reduces nausea, which helps prevent the stomach discomfort some people experience with turmeric supplements. Clinical research confirms the combination provides synergistic anti-inflammatory effects exceeding either ingredient individually.' } },
