  { '@type': 'Question', name: 'Are there side effects from turmeric and ginger gummies?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Both turmeric and ginger are generally well-tolerated at recommended doses. Potential side effects include: mild gastrointestinal discomfort (nausea, diarrhea) at high doses, especially on an empty stomach. Turmeric/curcumin may interact with blood thinners (warfarin, aspirin) by enhancing anticoagulant effects — consult your doctor if you take anticoagulant medications. High-dose ginger (more than 4g daily) may increase bleeding risk and interact with anticoagulants. Both turmeric and ginger may lower blood sugar, potentially enhancing the effects of diabetes medications. Turmeric may increase bile production and should be avoided by people with gallbladder disease or bile duct obstruction. Discontinue both supplements 2 weeks before scheduled surgery due to mild anticoagulant properties.' } },
